  "texts": [
    "The features in dynamic sign language recognition can be divided into local features, global features, and fusion features.",
    "Local feature mainly extracts local feature points with obvious changes in image sequence, mainly including corners, interest points, etc., to find corresponding points and regions in the image.",
    "Global features extract features based on depth images, including texture, shape, etc., to obtain the representation information of images.",
    "Fusion features mainly include global features and local features.",
    "Gray Level Co-Occurrence MatrixRepeated changes in grayscale distribution in spatial position form the texture."
  ],
